Description: OpenLand is an open-source R package for the analysis of land use
    and land cover  time series. It includes support for loading multitemporal
    gridded datasets; extraction of LULC transition matrices; determination of
    net and loss changes; performing a complete LULCC intensity analysis; and 
    visualization of LULCC and outcomes of intensity analysis using various 2D plots.
